\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves setaceous; silica-bodies saddle-shaped or rounded; slender 2-celled micro-hairs present; ligule membranous. Inflorescence a unilateral spike. Spikelets all hermaphrodite, triangular in section, with 1 floret. Glumes persistent, the lower very small, the upper usually absent. Lemma chartaceous, with a terminal awn. Palea hyaline, 2-keeled. Lodicules absent. Stamens 3. Ovary glabrous; style 1; stigma papillose. Grain with a short, linear hilum; starch-grains compound. Chromosomes large; basic number 13.
