\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. spartum} L.,{\i  Gen. Pl.} ed. 5, [522] (1754). Rhizome and bases of erect shoots covered with coriaceous scales. Stems up to 70 cm, wiry, solid. Leaves up to c. 50 cm × 1·5 mm, rigid, very tough; sheaths glabrous; ligule c. 7 mm, acute. Inflorescence-sheath 3-4(-9) cm, ovate, acute or with a leaf-like point. Spikelet protruding from the side of the sheath at maturity and falling entire. Lemma c. 2 cm. Palea 3-4 cm. Anthers c. 15 mm. 2n = 40. {\i Dry, sandy or clayey, often gypsaceous soils. Mediterranean region}. *Bl Cr Hs It Sa Si.
